{"lemma":"شَيْبانٌ","slug":"شَيْبانٌ","root":"ش.#.ب","root_slug":"ش-_-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-_-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23458","n23459"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23458","headword_ar":"شَيْبَانُ","root":"$yb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oyabu","text_ar":"اَشْيَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; near the end of the paragraph: ―         -b2-  and see also the paragraph here following."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n23459","headword_ar":"شِيبَانُ","root":"$yb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miloHaAnu","text_ar":"مِلْحَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) thus in a verse of El-Kumeyt, as related by Ibn-Selemeh, with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$","text_ar":"ش"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or the former word is written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayobaAnu","text_ar":"شَيْبَانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iybaAnu","text_ar":"شِيبَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the latter is as above, (K,) and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maloHaAnu","text_ar":"مَلْحَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two months of winter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA;) [as though meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the second of the Six Seasons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"commencing two months after the autumnal equinox; (see the former of the two tables in p. 1254;)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahoraA qimaAHK","text_ar":"شَهْرَا قِمَاحٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K, TA,) which are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two coldest months;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA;) so called because of the earth's being then white with snow and hoar frost; (S, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"falling at the period of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"auroral"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rising of the Scorpion and the Vulture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaqorab","text_ar":"العَقْرَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~asor","text_ar":"النَّسْر"},{"kind":"text","text":", [by which latter is meant"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~asoru AlwaAqiEu","text_ar":"النَّسْرُ الوَاقِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. the star a of Lyra,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"said by him who knows not to be the two Kánoons"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnuwnu AlA^aw~alu","text_ar":"كَانُونُ الاَوَّلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnuwnu Alv~aAniY","text_ar":"كَانُونُ الثَّانِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", corresponding to December and January O.S.]: (TA:) [it appears that they nearly agree with the two Kánoons; for El-Kazweenee and others say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqalobu","text_ar":"القَلْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. the heart of the Scorpion, which is the 18th of the Mansions of the Moon,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~asoru AlwaAqiEu","text_ar":"النَّسْرُ الوَاقِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"rise together, and their auroral rising in Central Arabia, about the commencement of the era of the Flight, accord. to my calculation, (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAzilu Alqamari","text_ar":"مَنَازِلُ القَمَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nzl","text_ar":"نزل"},{"kind":"text","text":",) was on the 25th of November O. S.: see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miloHaAnu","text_ar":"مِلْحَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qimaAHN","text_ar":"قِمَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is also said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iybaAnu","text_ar":"شِيبَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[used alone] is a name of ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the month"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kAnwn AlAw~l","text_ar":"كانون الاوّل"},{"kind":"text","text":", because of the whiteness of the earth by reason of the hoar-frost and snow. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B4%D9%8A%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86/","headword_ar":"شيبانية","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23350#460bb9","body_html":"<span>الشيبانية: هم أصحاب شيبان بن سلمة، قالوا بالجبر ونفي القدر.</span>"}]}}